title: *** $1,530 / 2 BR SEPT. 1ST SOUTH  MINNEAPOLIS CLASSIC 20'S UPPER****
posting_body: ["*** $1,530 / 2 BEDROOM - CLASSIC 20'S UPPER FLOOR DUPLEX AVAILABLE SEPTEMBER 1ST (16TH AVE S. & 37TH ST.)", ' Some flexibility for earlier move in.', 'SOUTH MINNEAPOLIS, POWDERHORN NEIGHBORHOOD', 'Attractive 2 BEDROOM Upper floor apt.', 'in duplex on a quiet block.', '1,150 SF', 'Original woodwork and built-in cabinets, ceiling fans throughout, great storage, hardwood floors, full bath with tiled floor, classic claw foot tub, pedestal sink and subway tiled walls.', 'Ample storage in kitchen’s tall wood cabinets.', 'Kitchen has gas stove, fridge, microwave and dishwasher.', 'Plentiful on-street parking.', 'Bright sunny, southern & western exposure, especially nice during the winter months!', 'Efficient hot water boiler heat!', 'AMENITIES:', 'FREE LAUNDRY on-site in basement', 'Free basement storage,', 'Back yard patio with plenty of room for your grill,', 'Room for shared garden', 'Second floor balcony for plants', 'Ample street parking,', 'AC: three (3) window units included', 'Tenant pays utilities (gas, electric, water, trash)', "Near May Day Cafe, Everett's Meats, Black Eyed Roasting Co, Sister Sludge Coffee Cafe Wine Bar, Carbone's, Tom's Popcorn, Italian Eatery and the famous Juicy Lucy at Matt's Bar.", 'BUS LINES: Easy access to bus lines (23, 22, 14, 111),', '1 Block from bus line on Bloomington Ave.  & 38th St.  / 5 blocks from Cedar Ave bus routes', 'Near light rail, airport, U of M, 35W & Hiawatha Ave / 62 corridors, great city parks, trails and paths along Minnehaha Creek.', 'Proximity to Minnehaha Creek, Powderhorn Park and Lake Nokomis,', '10 minutes east of the Chain of Lakes, Eat Street and Uptown area.', 'Tenant simply enjoys the space!', '$1,530/month rent plus utilities,', 'No smoking, no pets.', "Security deposit equal to one month's rent.", 'One rental application per adult.', 'LEASE START DATE AUGUST 1ST.', 'CALL, TEXT OR EMAIL PETE @', 'C:', 'show contact info', 'SHOWINGS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY.']
